  - atc_3: Zonisamide is pharmacologically related to antiepileptics and antiinfectives and antiseptics, excl. combinations with corticosteroids.
  - atc_4: The chemical and functional group of  is other antiepileptics and sulfonamides.
  - category: Zonisamide is part of Agents causing hyperkalemia ; Amides ; Anti-epileptic Agent ; Antiarrhythmic agents ; Anticonvulsants ; Bradycardia-Causing Agents ; Calcium Channel Blockers ; Calcium-Regulating Hormones and Agents ; Carbonic Anhydrase Inhibitors ; Cardiovascular Agents ; Central Nervous System Agents ; Central Nervous System Depressants ; Compounds used in a research, industrial, or household setting ; Cytochrome P-450 CYP2C19 Inhibitors ; Cytochrome P-450 CYP2C19 Inhibitors (weak) ; Cytochrome P-450 CYP2C19 Substrates ; Cytochrome P-450 CYP3A Substrates ; Cytochrome P-450 CYP3A4 Substrates ; Cytochrome P-450 CYP3A5 Substrates ; Cytochrome P-450 Enzyme Inhibitors ; Cytochrome P-450 Substrates ; Decreased Central Nervous System Disorganized Electrical Activity ; Diuretics ; Drugs that are Mainly Renally Excreted ; Genito Urinary System and Sex Hormones ; Gynecological Antiinfectives and Antiseptics ; Isoxazoles ; Membrane Transport Modulators ; Monoamine Oxidase A Inhibitors for interaction with Monoamine Oxidase A substrates ; Nervous System ; P-glycoprotein inhibitors ; Potential QTc-Prolonging Agents ; QTc Prolonging Agents ; Sulfonamides ; Sulfones ; Sulfur Compounds ; UGT1A1 Substrates.
